HEADWORD: Huckaback
<hw>Huck"a*back</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perh. orig.,
peddler's wares; cf. LG. <ets>hukkebak</ets> pickback. Cf.
<er>Huckster</er>.]</ety> <def>A kind of linen cloth with raised
figures, used for towelings.</def>⟦br⟧
